article.story: DAVIDSON, N.C. -- — Connor Kochera had 23 points in Davidson's 69-45 win against Boston University on Tuesday night. Kochera was 10 of 12 shooting (2 for 3 from 3-point range) for the Wildcats (3-2). Reed Bailey added 12 points while finishing 6 of 9 from the floor, and they also had eight rebounds. Grant Huffman was 4 of 9 shooting (1 for 3 from 3-point range) to finish with 10 points. The Terriers (1-4) were led by Matai Baptiste, who recorded 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
